articles.author: Philip Blenkinsop
articles.description: Voters in 21 EU countries including France and Germany will conclude a four-day election for the European Parliament on Sunday, which is expected to shift the assembly to the right and boost the numbers of eurosceptic nationalists.
articles.title: European Parliament poised for rightward shift after final voting

articles.author: Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Netanyahu will lose the backing of a centrist bloc that has helped broaden support for the government in Israel and abroad, at a time of increasing diplomatic and domestic pressure eight months into the Gaza war.
articles.title: Israel's centrist minister Benny Gantz quits Netanyahu government

articles.author: Michel Rose, Tassilo Hummel
articles.description: The president said the results were a disaster for his government, and one he could not pretend to ignore.
articles.title: Macron calls shock French elections after far-right rout by Le Pen

articles.author: James Mackenzie
articles.description: Gantz was one of the few in Israel's government who still appeared to enjoy U.S. confidence.
articles.title: Benny Gantz, man in the middle squeezed out by Israel's Netanyahu

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel's military said a special forces officer was killed in exchanges of fire with militants emerging from cover in residential blocks, and that it knew of "under 100" Palestinians killed, though not how many of them were militants or civilians.
articles.title: Israel pounds central Gaza as Palestinian death toll in hostage rescue raid rises to 274

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Seoul was following through on a warning demanding that Pyongyang stop sending balloons carrying trash into the South.
articles.title: North Korea leader's sister warns of new response against South Korean loudspeakers, leaflets

articles.author: Ronald Popeski
articles.description: Chasiv Yar stands on high ground west of Bakhmut, a town Russian forces seized a year ago. It is seen by both sides as a potential staging point for Russia to advance on the key cities of Kramatorsk and Sloviansk.
articles.title: Russia appears to make headway in key Ukrainian town of Chasiv Yar

articles.author: Jan Strupczewski
articles.description: The rise of euro-sceptic nationalist parties in the European election is likely to complicate Ursula von der Leyen's bid to get a second term as president of the powerful European Commission, though she remains the front-runner for the job.
articles.title: Euro-sceptic gains in EU election complicate von der Leyen's Commission bid

articles.author: Philip Blenkinsop, Charlotte Van Campenhout
articles.description: Flemish nationalist party N-VA (New Flemish Alliance) was on course to remain the largest party in Belgium's parliament as the liberals of Prime Minister Alexander De Croo slumped, setting the country on course for months of challenging coalition talks.
articles.title: Flemish nationalists set to retain lead in Belgian parliament, PM's liberals take hit

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The European Parliament took a shift to the right after a four-day election concluded on Sunday, with more eurosceptic nationalists and fewer mainstream liberals and Greens.
articles.title: Explainer: From trade to climate, five takeaways from the EU election
